text.section:
A prospective juror is disqualified to serve on a jury if the juror:
Is under eighteen (18) years of age;
Is not a citizen of the United States;
Is not a resident of the county;
Has insufficient knowledge of the English language;
Has been previously convicted of a felony and has not been pardoned or received a restoration of civil rights by the Governor or other authorized person of the jurisdiction in which the person was convicted;
Is presently under indictment; or
Has served on a jury within the time limitations set out under KRS 29A.130.
